Below some references that helped me both to understand the theories and methods of machine learning and to code these Python scripts:

* Machine learning course 
[[1]](https://www.kaggle.com/datasets/hojjatk/mnist-dataset)
- Jean-Paul Haton, Emmanuel Haton et Marie-Christine Haton. INTELLIGENCES ARTIFICIELLES: de la théorie à la pratique. Modèles, applications et enjeux des IA. Edition DUNOD (2023). ISBN 978-2-10-085892-7
- Chloé-Agathe Azencott. Introduction au Machine Learning. 2e édition DUNOD. (2022). ISBN 978-2-10-083476-1. 
- Arnaud Bodin et François Recher. DEEPMATH Mathématiques (simples) des réseaux de neurones (pas trop compliqués). Publication indépendante (2021). ISBN 979-8-69-267287-2.

* Python language and TensorFlow
- TensorFlow tutorials website: https://www.tensorflow.org/tutorials. 
- Keras 3 API documentation: https://keras.io/api/

* Research papers
- Srivastava, Nitish, et al. "Dropout: A Simple Way to Prevent Neural Networks from Overfitting." Journal of Machine Learning Research, vol. 15, no. 56, 2014, pp. 1929–1958, http://jmlr.org/papers/v15/srivastava14a.html.
- Li, Lisha, et al. "Hyperband: A Novel Bandit-Based Approach to Hyperparameter Optimization." Journal of Machine Learning Research, vol. 18, no. 185, 2018, pp. 1–52, http://jmlr.org/papers/v18/16-558.html.
- Kingma, Diederik P., and Jimmy Ba. "Adam: A Method for Stochastic Optimization." arXiv preprint, 2017, https://arxiv.org/abs/1412.6980.
